textBody:
Johann Sebastian Bach (1685–1750) was a famous German composer of the Baroque period.

Bach may also refer to:

Broadcasting

* WBQK, a radio station licensed to West Point, Virginia, United States, known as Bach FM
* WLTT, a radio station licensed to Carolina Beach, North Carolina, United States, known as Bach FM from 2011 to 2013

Organizations

* The Brown Association for Cooperative Housing, in Providence, Rhode Island, United States
* Vincent Bach Corporation, a brass instrument manufacturer

People

* Bach family, of importance in the history of music
* Bach (surname)
* Bach (actor) (Charles-Joseph Pasquier, 1882–1953), French actor, singer and music hall performer
* Bill Bachrach (1879–1959), American swim coach known as "Bach"
*King Bach, famous youtuber and viner
* Yoel Sirkis (1561–1640), Polish posek and halakhist, known as "the Bach"

Places

* Bach, Austria, a municipality in Reutte
* Bach, Lot, a commune in France
* Bach, Michigan, an unincorporated community in Sebewaing Township
* Bach an der Donau, a town in Regensburg, Bavaria, Germany
* Bach Ice Shelf, on Alexander Island, Antarctica
* Bach quadrangle, on the planet Mercury
* Bach (crater), on the planet Mercury
* Bäch, a settlement of the Freienbach municipality in Schwyz, Switzerland
** Bäch railway station, in Freienbach, Switzerland

Other uses

* Bach (journal), an academic journal of Baroque music
* Bach (New Zealand), a modest holiday home or beach house
* 1814 Bach, an asteroid
* BACH motif, a sequence of notes
